HEADWORD: Deleterious
<hw>Del`e*te"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>deleterius</ets> noxious, Gr. <grk>dhlhth`rios</grk>, fr.
<grk>dhlei^sqai</grk> to hurt, damage; prob. akin to L.
<ets>delere</ets> to destroy.]</ety> <def>Hurtful; noxious; destructive;
pernicious; <as>as, a <ex>deleterious</ex> plant or quality; a
<ex>deleterious</ex> example.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Del`e*te"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Del`e*te"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

